**Files affected:** `frontend/core/reporter_html.py`, JS in report HTML template

---

### 🟡 P4.2 — Dry-run (view last results without running)
**Why medium:** Lets operators review the most recent health status without triggering a new check run — useful for quick status reviews or during maintenance windows.
**Status: NOT STARTED** — depends on P3.1; no Dry Run button

**Tasks:**
- New "Dry Run" button in the UI (distinct from "Run Health Check")
- Loads and renders the most recent results from the history DB without contacting any bastion
- Report view clearly labeled "Dry Run — showing results from [last run timestamp]"
- No bastion writes, no SSH, no lock acquisition — purely a DB read and render
- Stores the view event in DB with `source='dry_run'` for audit trail

**Files affected:** `frontend/static/index.html`, `frontend/app.py`, `frontend/core/history_db.py`

