## Priority 5 — Automation Tier

### 🟡 P5.1 — CLI headless mode
**Why medium:** Enables CI/CD integration and scripting. Less urgent than UI features but unlocks new use cases.
**Status: NOT STARTED** — `main.py` has minimal arg parsing only; no headless run, no JSON output, no exit code semantics

**Tasks:**
- New entry point in existing `main.py`: `cloudhealth run --clusters prod-east --checks etcd,nodes --output json --no-browser`
- Reuses existing backend orchestration code (no frontend HTTP/browser)
- Outputs JSON to stdout for piping
- Exit codes: 0 = all pass, 1 = any warnings, 2 = any failures or errors
- `--quiet` flag for minimal output (just exit code)
- `--diff` flag to compare against last run from history DB
- CLI runs are written to history DB with `source='cli'` (per P3.1 schema)
- Document examples in README for cron, GitHub Actions, etc.

**Files affected:** `main.py`, new `frontend/core/cli_runner.py`

---

### 🟢 P5.2 — Scheduled daily runs per cluster
**Why low:** Multiplies value of everything else, but requires P3.1 (history DB) and P2.1 (clean cancel) to be solid first. Don't build before foundation is rock-solid.
**Status: NOT STARTED**

**Tasks:**
- New "Schedules" tab in frontend showing existing schedules per cluster
- Per-cluster cron expression (e.g., "0 6 * * *" = daily 6am, or after 1 hr execute)
- Enable/disable toggle per schedule
- Backend daemon mode: `python3 main.py --daemon`
- Daemon polls `schedules` table every minute, triggers runs at scheduled times
- Lock check before starting scheduled run — must NOT conflict with manual runs
- Results written to history DB with `source='scheduled'`
- Webhook field per schedule (POST to URL with summary JSON on completion) — foundation for Slack/email alerts

**Files affected:** new `backend/scheduler.py`, `frontend/static/index.html`, `frontend/app.py`, `frontend/core/history_db.py`

